---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Fresh Beginnings Publishing — already fast, made findable — Gian Trotta"
  description="A children's book publisher's site scored perfect on Google's speed test but had no sitemap, no search previews, and identical titles on every page. Here's what changed."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pb-12 pt-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">Case study · Site refresh</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
      Fresh Beginnings Publishing — already fast, made findable
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-mist">
      Michelle's book-marketing site was already fast — under a second on mobile, 100 on Google's
      speed test. But search engines and AI assistants had almost nothing to go on. Two days later
      it had a real findability layer, a visual refresh, and a verified spot in Google Search
      Console.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 font-utility text-sm text-mist">
      <a
        href="https://www.freshbeginningspublishing.com/"
        class="text-steel underline hover:text-ink"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
      >
        freshbeginningspublishing.com
      </a>
      · children's book publisher · Northeast Ohio
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Receipt strip: the headline numbers -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-white" aria-label="Before and after summary">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10">
      <div class="receipt-wrap mx-auto max-w-2xl">
        <div class="receipt-paper px-7 py-8 font-utility">
          <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Site checkup · before → after</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Search setup</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">none</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">complete</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Page titles</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">1 shared title</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">unique on every page</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Google Search Console</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">not set up</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">verified · sitemap live</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4">
              <dt>Google best-practices score</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold text-steel">96 → 100</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
      Perfect speed scores hid a bigger gap
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-mist">
      <p>
        Fresh Beginnings Publishing promotes <em>Rusty the Raccoon is Scared of the Dark</em>, a
        children's book Michelle wrote and illustrated. I ran my usual site checkup and the speed
        numbers were already great — under a second to load on a phone, 100 out of 100 on Google's
        test.
      </p>
      <p>
        None of that mattered for search. The site had no sitemap, no robots file, no link
        previews for social shares, and no structured data describing the publisher or the book.
        All seven pages used the same title and description, so Google saw one page repeated
        seven times.
      </p>
      <p>
        Three of those pages — Careers, Press, and Shop — were leftover placeholders from when the
        publishing company was still active, and they were still live and indexable. Google could
        easily read them as duplicate content. Fast, sure. But nobody could find it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we did -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">What I did</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Built the findability layer, then refreshed the look
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="space-y-5 text-mist">
          <p>
            I started with a full audit — the same checkup I run for any local business owner who
            thinks their site is "fine because it loads fast." It confirmed the gap wasn't speed.
            It was everything Google and AI tools need to understand what the site is and
            recommend it.
          </p>
          <p>
            From there, I rebuilt the site with a complete search layer: a sitemap and robots file,
            unique titles and descriptions on every page, link previews for social sharing,
            structured data for the publisher and the book, and a plain-text file so AI assistants
            can read what the business offers. I verified Google Search Console and submitted the
            sitemap the same day the new site went live.
          </p>
          <p>
            I pulled the three dead-end placeholder pages and dropped the Instagram link since that
            account was gone. Facebook and YouTube stayed, along with the cross-link to the book's
            dedicated site at rustytheraccoon.com — Fresh Beginnings is still the publisher of
            record.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-mist">
          <p>
            With the invisible work solid, I moved on to how the site looks and reads: a warmer
            typeface, an accent color pulled from Michelle's mushroom illustration, a homepage
            section that showcases the book, and refreshed About and Contact pages. A custom 404
            page and a storybook-style empty state for the blog (still waiting on its first post)
            round it out.
          </p>
          <p>
            Speed stayed perfect through the redesign — no heavy scripts, no page-builder bloat. It
            loads just as fast on phones and desktops as before, with a cleaner layout on tall
            screens and navigation that actually works on iPads, not just desktop with a mouse.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Before / after screenshots -->
      <figure class="mt-12 border border-line bg-porcelain p-4 sm:p-6">
        <figcaption class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">
          Homepage · before and after
        </figcaption>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div>
            <p class="mb-2 font-utility text-sm font-bold text-ink">Before</p>
            <img
              src="/case-studies/fresh-beginnings/before.png"
              alt="Fresh Beginnings Publishing homepage before the refresh — original layout with mint green hero and mushroom illustration"
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full border border-line"
            />
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="mb-2 font-utility text-sm font-bold text-ink">After</p>
            <img
              src="/case-studies/fresh-beginnings/after.png"
              alt="Fresh Beginnings Publishing homepage after the refresh — updated typography, ochre accent, and book section"
              width="1440"
              height="900"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full border border-line"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">Results</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
      Measurable, not just nicer
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg text-mist">
      Every number below comes from Lighthouse reports against the live site — before on July 16,
      after on July 17. Speed was already fine going in. The wins here are findability and polish.
    </p>

    <dl class="mt-10 grid gap-px border border-line bg-line sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      <div class="bg-white p-5">
        <dt class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Search setup</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 font-utility text-xl font-bold text-flare">0 → complete</dd>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-mist">
          Sitemap, robots file, link previews, structured data, and AI-readable site summary added.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-5">
        <dt class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Google Search Console</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 font-utility text-xl font-bold text-steel">Live</dd>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-mist">
          Property verified and sitemap processed the day the new site shipped.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-5">
        <dt class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Best-practices score</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 font-utility text-xl font-bold text-steel">96 → 100</dd>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-mist">
          Fixed a broken favicon request and cleaned up leftover placeholder pages.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-5">
        <dt class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">Mobile load time</dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 font-utility text-xl font-bold text-steel">0.9 s</dd>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-mist">
          Still under a second on a phone. Page weight dropped from 28 KiB to 25 KiB.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>

    <div class="mt-10 overflow-x-auto border border-line bg-white">
      <table class="w-full min-w-[32rem] text-left text-sm">
        <caption class="sr-only">
          Google Lighthouse scores before and after the Fresh Beginnings site refresh
        </caption>
        <thead class="border-b border-line bg-porcelain font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mist">
          <tr>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-normal">Category</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-normal">Before (mobile)</th>
            <th scope="col" class="px-5 py-4 font-normal">After (mobile)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-line">
          <tr>
            <th scope="row" class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold">Speed</th>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility">100</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility font-bold text-steel">100</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row" class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold">Accessibility</th>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility">100</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility font-bold text-steel">100</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row" class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold">Best practices</th>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility">96</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility font-bold text-flare-deep">100</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th scope="row" class="px-5 py-4 font-semibold">Search basics (Lighthouse)</th>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility">100</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-4 font-utility font-bold text-steel">100</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="border-t border-line px-5 py-4 text-sm text-mist">
        Lighthouse's search score only checks a handful of basics — the old site already passed
        while missing a sitemap, structured data, and unique page titles. The real findability work
        sits below what that number measures.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-mist">
      Desktop scores matched: 100 across the board before and after, with best practices moving from
      96 to 100. Layout shift on mobile went from a small wobble to zero.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Fit + CTA -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">Sound familiar?</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Your site might be fast and still invisible
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-lg text-mist">
        <p>
          If your site loads fine but you never show up when someone searches for what you do — or
          when they ask an AI assistant for a recommendation nearby — a Site Checkup is the place
          to start. I'll tell you plainly what's missing and what a fix would look like.
        </p>
        <p>
          Fresh Beginnings complements the Rusty the Raccoon rescue I did — that one was a slow Wix
          site with a monthly bill, this one was already fast on modern hosting. Different starting
          points, same outcome: found on Google, ready for AI search, built to stay that way.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/contact/"
          class="bg-flare-deep px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-porcelain hover:bg-flare"
        >
          Book a free 15-minute call
        </a>
        <a href="/services/" class="border border-ink px-6 py-3 font-semibold hover:bg-ink hover:text-porcelain">
          See services
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
